# Files NOT to send into the Docker build context. Without this,
# every `docker build` ships the entire repo (including target/,
# node_modules, .git, evadex_outputs, etc.) over to the daemon —
# wasting bandwidth, time, and cache invalidation budget for no
# build benefit.
#
# Keep this file the same across every Dockerfile in deploy/ —
# they all use the repo root as build context. If a particular
# Dockerfile genuinely needs one of these directories, list it
# explicitly via `COPY` after a `!path` un-ignore (none today).

# --- Rust build artifacts -------------------------------------------------
# `target/` is the elephant. The local cargo cache rebuilds inside the
# Docker image, so shipping host-side build artifacts is pure waste.
target/
**/target/

# --- UI build artifacts ---------------------------------------------------
# The Next.js SPA is rebuilt inside deploy/nginx/Dockerfile via pnpm.
# Sending the host's node_modules + .next blows the build context up
# by hundreds of megabytes for files the build will replace anyway.
ui/node_modules/
ui/.next/
ui/out/
ui/.turbo/

# --- Version control ------------------------------------------------------
.git/
.gitignore
.github/

# --- IDE / editor / OS scratch -------------------------------------------
.vscode/
.idea/
.cursor/
*.swp
*.swo
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# --- Local environment / secrets -----------------------------------------
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
*.pem
*.key

# --- Tooling output / coverage / fixtures --------------------------------
# evadex_outputs/ holds adversarial-test artifacts that aren't part of
# any image build. coverage/ is local-only.
evadex_outputs/
coverage/
*.profraw
*.profdata

# --- Documentation that doesn't ship in containers -----------------------
# Dockerfile.api intentionally COPYs README.md + docs/ for siphon-api's
# include_str! at compile time. Don't list those here.
BENCHMARKS_RAW.md
*.tmp
